Experts have expressed concern over neglect of mother tongue by government and the society in general and counsel on the need to save it from extinction. A Sociologist, Dr Raymond Adaramodu of department of Language and Literature, Osun State College of Education, Ila Orangun noted that the importance of mother tongue cannot be over emphasised. He pointed out that ordinarily, thought of a human being is conveyed and transmitted into action through the mother tongue. He however regretted that Yoruba language was reduced to nothing by Education policy and curriculum formulators who classified mother tongues as vernacular and therefore an aberration for our children adding that to safe the scenario, pride of place must be accorded mother tongue. Corroborating him, the Executive Secretary, Art and Culture in Osun State Mr. Tunde Oyesiji said there is the urgent need to redeem the image of mother tongue in the society especially among the young ones if it will not go into extinction. He noted that avoidance of mother tongue is an indirect way of losing one’s culture and identity because language forms the basis for the development of human existence. 